Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi says police are pulling out all the stops to find suspects in the murder of the Phomoleong Secondary School deputy principal. She was gunned down in the driveway of the Tembisa school on Friday. Reporter Heidi Giokos has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG -  Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi says work is underway to find the killers of the deputy principal of Phomolong Secondary school in Tembisa. READ: Deputy principal shot and killed He says a plan is in place to track the culprits. Lesufi visited the school this morning after Friday's shooting. #Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA Lesufi is also warning schools have become targets for criminals. He's urging police to do their part in protecting education institutions. Lesufi says the sector deserves to be protected. Those behind the killing of your deputy principal will be found. That's the promise Gauteng Education  MEC,  Panyaza Lesufi made to teachers and pupils at  Phomolong Secondary School in  Tembisa. eNCA's Heidi Giokos has more details. Courtesy #DStv403